DOM in Javascript:
    - Document Object Model.
    - we will access, modify and update the UI.
    - DOM use tree data structure.
    -apply CSS & get info cal to return
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
 body UI-DOM- script(logic).

 Document-<html></html>
Element node- all the html tags body,div,p.. etc
attribute node-
        eg <a href="xyz.html">Click here</a>
        href,src is an attribute node.
text node-The text between the start tag & end tag is call it as text node.
        e.g in above example is "Click here".

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Ref Dom tree structure:
http://w3schools.sinsixx.com/htmldom/dom_nodetree.asp.htm

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
**DOM Methods(Document)
1>document.getElementById("")
2>document.getElementByClassname("")
3>document.getElementByTagname("")

HTML DOM Methods
x.getElementById(id) - get the element with a specified id
x.getElementsByTagName(name) - get all elements with a specified tag name
x.appendChild(node) - insert a child node to x
x.removeChild(node) - remove a child node from x
Note: In the list above, x is a node object (HTML element).

